      "id": "E:note:row328302:1",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Respiratory failure, acute (not ARDS/[**Doctor Last Name **])    Assessment:    ",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row328302#s1",
      "text": "Respiratory failure, acute (not ARDS/[**Doctor Last Name **])    Assessment:    Obtained pt on 6LNC and FT 100% fiO2, sats on these settings ~88%,    breath sounds clear to right lung and dim to left, no Cxray this am, pt    with increased confusion, orientedx1 consistant with previous    assessment, unable to follow command without aggressive cues, unable to    say last name or birth date, increasingly somulant    Action:    Pt placed on high flow neb at 95% fiO2, obtained vbg and abg, see    flowsheet for objective data, pt with elevation in PCO2, sats at this    time ~90% on high flow neb, attempted nasal bipap, not able to maintain    sats on nasal bipap, started full mask, continued difficulties    ventilating, pt increasingly lethargic during this time, HO contact[**Name (NI) **]    pts HCP to confirm [**Name (NI) **], at 1400 intubated pt, AC 0.70/500/14/+8, Cxray,    repeat abg obtained, tapped pleural effusions fluid sent to micro,    post- procedure Cxray done    Response:    Ongoing,  tube placement confirmed by Cxray, breath sounds clear,    maintaining sats on 70% fiO2    Plan:    f/u results of repeat ABG, if not improved and need for frequent ABGs ?    need for a-line placement,, continue mechanical vent as needed with    resolution of hypercarbia, f/u post thoracentisis xray, follow-up micro    data    Abdominal pain (including abdominal tenderness)    Assessment:    Pt with largely distended abd, no BM for several days, neg flatus,    vague reports of abg pain    Action:    Pt given fleets enema with no effect, colace as ordered    Response:    No BM at this time    Plan:    Continue bowel regiment, increase as needed, ? placement of rectal tube    for decompression if otherwise unable to resolve    Atrial fibrillation (Afib)    Assessment:    Obtained pt on dilt gtt 10mg/hr and amiodarone 200 mg po, NSR 70s no    ectopy    Action:    d/c d dilt gtt with no change in rate or rhythm noted, amiodarone    d/c d, pt ordered for qid lopressor for rate control, peri-intubation    HR 50s-60s, post intubation HR 50s to mid 40s, consulted pharmacy about    ?sedation in the setting of mental retardation (MR) of unknown    etiology, continuing to monitor tele, holding lopressor for SB    Response:    Ongoing, pt remains of cardiac gtts, in NSR/SB    Plan:    f/u pharm recs, titrate sedation to hemodynamics and comfort, continue    to monitor tele"
    }
  ],
